The 36 Righteous Ones, the basis of the Djoric-Dmatix Proposal, is an especially important concept in the branch of Judaism being tested. As such, when a Hasidic Jew uses 475, they're converted into an additional instance of them. The reference to Humes is a retcon/reframing of the Proposal's  idea into something scientific, something based on newer site concepts.








