08 Oct 2018 23:18






I'm not in agreement with this. The Foundation isn't just a prison, it's an enormous science lab. Their goal is to create that structure that understands the anomalies - else, why both running tests and experiments? Why bother exploring? Why do anything other than lock the anomalies away under lock and key? Heck, why not just destroy as many as possible? Containment achieves nothing that destruction doesn't achieve better when it comes to security.

It's because the essence of the Foundation has never just been containment. It's also been testing, experimenting, exploring, and learning. From learning comes understanding. From understanding can come entire branches of study, new science, new technology. Advancing enough that you can quantitatively measure certain things that couldn't be measured before isn't a cop-out, it's exactly what the Foundation, if it is at all effective in its efforts, SHOULD be getting to.

As for releasing itwell, they can't release that without also bringing awareness to a whole bunch of things that might cause a whole hell of a lot of trouble. Any brand-new science brings paradigm shifts, which can cause as much bad as good - and given the Foundation deals with a lot of things that will Kill You Right Dead Or Worse, it's probably not something they want to throw out there haphazardly.







